article.headline: Cal Poly 73, Cal St.-Fullerton 67
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Chris Eversley scored 18 points off the bench and Cal Poly-San Luis Obispo ran off 18 consecutive points in the first half in a 73-67 victory over Cal State Fullerton on Saturday night. Dylan Royer added 12 points, Amaurys Fermin 11 and David Hanson 10 for the Mustangs (10-6, 1-2 Big West), who ended a two-game losing streak. Kwame Vaughn scored 18 points and D.J. Seeley 14 for the Titans (10-5, 2-2), who dropped their second in a row. The Titans led 9-7 before Cal Poly unleashed its game-changing run. The 18-0 spurt featured seven points by Maliik Love, who finished it off with a layup that made the score 25-9 with 10:47 left in the first half. The gap peaked at 22 early in the second half and was still 70-57 with 58 seconds to play before the Titans closed with a rush.
